<BaseLayout title="Sources" description="Primary data sources planned for UK Elections candidate, result, boundary, polling, and demographic context.">
  <section class="page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Sources</p>
    <h1>Source status comes before claims.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      This page tracks the public data feeds, internal pilots, and review gates planned for the
      first election datasets. Nothing here is presented as live coverage yet.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="source-table" aria-label="Planned data sources">
    <div><strong>Democracy Club</strong><span>Candidates, ballot metadata, and candidate result rows where available</span><em>Planned</em></div>
    <div><strong>Official notices</strong><span>Statements of persons nominated, local authority result pages, and returning officer declarations</span><em>Required</em></div>
    <div><strong>House of Commons Library</strong><span>Westminster constituency and candidate result files</span><em>Planned</em></div>
    <div><strong>Local archives</strong><span>Local Elections Archive Project, Open Council Data, DCLEAPIL, and local election handbooks</span><em>Review</em></div>
    <div><strong>ONSPD, Boundary-Line, ONS Geography</strong><span>Postcode, ward, division, constituency, and authority joins</span><em>Planned</em></div>
    <div><strong>Boundaries Scotland and Senedd resources</strong><span>Scottish Parliament, Scottish local, and Welsh election geography</span><em>Planned</em></div>
    <div><strong>UKD, Census, ONS/Nomis, IMD</strong><span>Ward and constituency demographic features with source metadata</span><em>Review</em></div>
    <div><strong>Polling records</strong><span>Pollster, client, fieldwork dates, sample, mode, geography, and method notes</span><em>Planned</em></div>
    <div><strong>Parliament and finance APIs</strong><span>Members, votes, Hansard, IPSA, Electoral Commission finance, Companies House, and interests data for context pages</span><em>Later</em></div>
    <div><strong>AI DOGE and Labour tracker</strong><span>Internal source review for refined local modelling and provenance workflows</span><em>Internal</em></div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
